name: 134 Scarboro Ave, Calgary, AB T3C 2H1, Canada
directions:
On the middle floor, there are multiple fully enclosed single-stall washrooms, one of which is wheelchair accessible, the sink area is gender-neutral as are all the individual stalls. The top floor has 2 gender-neutral washrooms located at the back of the sanctuary on the left-hand side (if you are looking at the pulpit).

Please note that this church welcomes people of all faiths, and identities (you will not be judged for any identity and are welcome)
comment:
Weekdays during "Office" hours:
If the side doors are open, ask the person in the office on your right if you can use the washroom mention you are looking for an accessible/gender-inclusive/changing table, and they will let you through no issue (they just like to know who is in the building). 
If the side doors are locked use the buzzer and make the same request.

Sunday Mornings: come on in the main sanctuary doors at the top of the hill, the follow the narrow isle on your left through to the doors and there will be 2 washrooms, if anyone asks just let them know that you are looking for a washroom. Feel free to stay or leave.
